Package net.objectzoo.ebc

This package contains interfaces that can be used to define EBCs.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CanProcess<ProcessParameter>
    An EBC that CanProcess is capable of processing input and thus provides an Action to do so.
    CanStart
    An EBC that CanStart can be invoked to perform some work and thus provides an Action0 to do so.
    Configurable
    EBCs that are Configurable can be configured with an arbitrary number of parameters.
    DependsOn<Dependency>
    An EBC that DependsOn another object, can be explicitly tagged with this interface.
    EntryPoint
    This is a special marker interface that can be used to tag an EBC as the EntryPoint of an application.
    ProcessAndResultFlow<ProcessParameter,ResultParameter>
    An EBC that is capable of processing input with a possible outcome of a result being sent.
    ProcessAndSignalFlow<ProcessParameter>
    An EBC that is capable of processing input with a possible outcome of a signal being sent.
    SendsResult<ResultParameter>
    An EBC that SendsResult is capable of sending the output of it's work to subscribed listeners and thus provides an Event to do so.
    SendsSignal
    An EBC that SendsSignal is capable of sending a signal when it's work completes to subscribed listeners and thus provides an Event0 to do so.
    StartAndResultFlow<ResultParameter>
    An EBC that is capable of being invoked with a possible outcome of a result being sent.
    StartAndSignalFlow
    An EBC that is capable of being invoked with a possible outcome of a signal being sent.

Package net.objectzoo.ebc Description

This package contains interfaces that can be used to define EBCs.
